article.headline: Green Bay 69, Wis.-Milwaukee 64
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Bryquis Perine scored 17 points Saturday as Wisconsin-Green Bay held on for a 69-64 victory over Wisconsin-Milwaukee. Rahmon Fletcher added 13 points for the Phoenix (8-9, 2/3 Horizon), and Steve Baker had 10 points and seven rebounds. For Milwaukee (8-9, 3-3), Kaylon Williams had 14 points, Tone Boyle 13, Anthony Hill 12 and Tony Meier 10. Hill also had 12 rebounds. Green Bay was on top 35-32 at halftime and increased that lead to as many as 18 points in the second half. Baker scored on a layup with 7:21 remaining to cap a 19-3 run and put the Phoenix on top 58-40. Fletcher had seven points during the run. Green Bay didn't make another field goal the rest of the game, but held on by hitting six of their final eight free-throw attempts. Milwaukee got as close as 68-64 with 16 seconds left when Meier hit a 3-pointer.
